<div class="patternContent"><div class="foswikiTopic"> <h1 id="Re_45parenting_a_topic">  Re-parenting a topic </h1>
<p></p>

The breadcrumbs (<a href="/bin/view/System/Contribs">Contribs</a> &gt; <a href="/bin/view/System/TipsContrib">TipsContrib</a> &gt; <a href="/bin/view/System/TipsOfTheDay">TipsOfTheDay</a>, for example) of any topic is constructed automatically in Foswiki by following the set topic parent. In the footer of a topic viewed with the default <a href="/bin/view/System/PatternSkin">PatternSkin</a> is a <strong>More topic actions</strong> link which will allow you to select a new parent for the page.
<p></p>

To re-parent a page:
To re-parent a topic:  <ol>
<li> Click <strong>More topic actions</strong> on the topic you wish to re-parent
</li> <li> Navigate to <strong>Set new topic parent</strong>
</li> <li> Begin typing a new parent topic name
</li> <li> Select a new parent from the list
</li> <li> Click on the <strong>Set new parent</strong> button
</li></ol> 
<p class='p'>You will notice that the breadcrumb will now reflect the new parent.</p>

<a href="/bin/view/System/TipsOfTheDay">See More Tips...</a></div>
<p class='p'></p>

